--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. TECHNICAL BASELINE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  • Target: macOS, SwiftUI, Xcode project Lifemaxxing.xcodeproj (current code
    is template ContentView only).
  • Persistence: choose one for v1 — SwiftData recommended (models map cleanly
    to entities above); migrate if you later need CloudKit sync.
  • Secrets: .env / API keys stay out of repo (see repo .gitignore); Notion
    experiment (main.js) is optional integration, not required for app v1.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. PHASED DELIVERY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Phase A — Foundation
  • Navigation structure; design tokens / spacing (optional: align with
    UI:UX design.rtf).
  • SwiftData (or chosen store) + seed or import for skill categories &
    questline shells.

Phase B — Dashboard + one vertical
  • Dashboard widgets wired to real (or stub) data.
  • Complete one skill category end-to-end (recommend Mental Health: mood +
    journal categories + wins) to prove EXP/stardust if modeled.

Phase C — Remaining skill + economy
  • Personal Care tasks; Household + Shopping List.
  • Wishlist + Shop UI; stardust earn/spend loop.

Phase D — Questlines + Map + weekly
  • Questline pages; todos/quests/subquests with deadlines.
  • Map aggregation; weekly quest templates and completion.

Phase E — Polish
  • Fit nutrition/training detail (meals/ingredients DBs), Fin workflows,
    weather widget, budget links — as you prioritize from outline.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. DEFINITION OF DONE (v1)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  • User can log mood, journal (with categories + daily entry), wins.
  • User can see and complete skill tasks for all three categories with
    deadlines and basic progress (EXP and/or stardust as implemented).
  • User can open all three questline hubs and record quests with deadlines.
  • Shop reads wishlist-style data; weekly quests can be checked off in-app.
  • Map shows at least a unified list or calendar of upcoming deadlines.

